--- On Fri, 13 Feb 2009, Tom Creighton wrote:
> Hello, I'm interested in registering as a Name Assigning Authority.  My
> organization is Family Search (familysearch.org) and is the largest
> genealogical association in the world.  As a leader in this field, we
> often find ourselves in the position to set direction for many other
> smaller genealogical societies and archives holding collections of
> genealogically significant artifacts.
> 
> Recognizing a need for our organization to address durability of
> published identifiers, and recognizing a similar need for our partner
> organizations, we have considered a number of different schemes.  While
> we are not entirely satisfied with ARK, it does appear that it addresses
> most of our concerns and has the benefit that we will not be creating yet
> another standard.
> 
> So to that end I'm contacting you to see what is required to register
> as a NAA.  In addition, I'd like to be able to communicate with someone
> involved in defining and extending the ARK specification, at the very
> least so I can ask questions about some of the areas of concern that we
> have.  So any information regarding associations I can join that will
> provide a forum for such interaction would be appreciated.
